{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Continuous auto-deploy: the running Gerrit environment reflects `main` without manual deploy or restart\n\n## Why\nLanding a change on `main` does NOT update the running environment. The **review-bot container's\ncode**, the site `replication.config`, and the g2p config all require a MANUAL deploy (SSM /\nsetup-*.sh) and sometimes a restart, causing drift + toil: epic 88ab S2's merge-review code landed\non `main` but the running `compose-review-bot-1` still runs the pre-S2 image; the S3\n`replication.config` fix had to be hand-applied via SSM. The deployed environment must AUTO-REFLECT\n`main` shortly after a change lands — WITHOUT ever destabilising the LIVE gate that contributors\ndepend on to review + submit.\n\n## What\n### Trigger — RESOLVED: a systemd timer on the Gerrit host (option a; NOT GitHub Actions→SSM)\n`rebar-autodeploy.timer` (every 2 min) runs `rebar-autodeploy.service` (oneshot). RATIONALE for the\non-box timer over a GitHub-Actions `deploy.yml`→SSM: (1) NO new trust surface — the box already has\nan instance role and reads the PUBLIC mirror READ-ONLY (no GitHub→AWS OIDC/`ssm:SendCommand` grant,\nwhich would make the GH runner a lateral-movement path into the box); (2) self-contained + simplest\nto back out; (3) ~2-min poll latency is fine for a deploy loop.\n\n### Deploy script (`infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh`, idempotent, flock-guarded)\n- **flock** `/var/lib/rebar/deploy.lock` (`-n`) — overlapping fires skip; a long deploy is never re-entered.\n- **deployed-sha** `/var/lib/rebar/deployed-sha`: on FIRST run (absent) INITIALIZE to the box's\n  current HEAD WITHOUT deploying (adopt current state); write atomically (`mv` tmp) ONLY after success.\n- **What to deploy (safety):** fetch `origin/main` from the mirror. The mirror's `main` only advances\n  via Gerrit SUBMIT (post two-vote gate) → its tip is Verified BY CONSTRUCTION; deploy ONLY that tip,\n  never an arbitrary ref. No-op when `origin/main == deployed-sha`.\n- **Change detection (path-set per component):** `git diff --name-only deployed-sha..origin/main` ∩ a\n  component manifest: review-bot (`src/rebar/**`, `Dockerfile.reviewbot`, `pyproject.toml`,\n  `docker-compose.yml`), replication (`replication.config`), g2p (`gerrit_to_platform.ini.template`,\n  `materialize-g2p-config.sh`).\n- **Per-component apply (only if changed):** review-bot → `docker tag` current image `:prev`, then\n  `docker compose up -d --build review-bot`; replication → re-materialise + autoReload (no restart);\n  g2p → `materialize-g2p-config.sh`.\n- **SCOPE BOUNDARY (v1):** covers review-bot container + replication.config + g2p config. `refs/meta/config`\n  (project.config) is OUT of v1 (rare, security-sensitive, needs an operator-only Gerrit admin key):\n  a change is DETECTED + signalled (metric + log), never auto-applied. Retry transient git/docker\n  failures 3× w/ backoff; persistent failure → fail-safe (leave prior state + marker).\n\n### Stability — live-pipeline safety (the load-bearing section)\nThe gate is FAIL-CLOSED: no LLM-Review vote ⇒ no submit. So a bad or careless deploy can FREEZE the\nwhole pipeline. Hardening:\n1. **Blast radius is bounded by construction.** Auto-deploy NEVER touches the `gerrit` container and\n   NEVER modifies `refs/meta/config` (the labels/submit-rules/ACLs). `docker compose` is invoked with\n   the EXPLICIT `review-bot` service only (never a bare `up` that could recreate `gerrit`); a guard\n   asserts the `gerrit` container id is unchanged across the deploy. Gate INTEGRITY is thus not\n   alterable by this mechanism — only the bot's code + replication/g2p config move.\n2. **No Gerrit restart, ever.** Config changes use `autoReload` (replication) / materialise (g2p); only\n   the review-bot CONTAINER restarts, and only when its code changed. Gerrit availability is untouched.\n3. **In-flight reviews are delayed, not lost.** A bot restart drops in-flight webhook processing, but\n   the EXISTING reconciler-backfill (events-log cursor) re-reviews any change missed during the\n   restart window — so a contributor's vote is at most DELAYED by one restart, never dropped. The\n   post-deploy health check confirms the reconciler loop is live.\n4. **A broken bot deploy self-heals (never freezes the gate).** After `up -d --build`, an END-TO-END\n   health check (30s timeout) verifies the bot is actually able to review (receiver `/health` + a\n   probe that the review path is functional), NOT merely that the process is up. On failure →\n   IMMEDIATE rollback to the `:prev` image + `up -d` + error marker; deployed-sha is NOT advanced. Max\n   gate-frozen window = the health-check timeout, then service is restored to the known-good image.\n5. **Circuit-breaker (no thrash on the live pipeline).** A per-target-SHA consecutive-failure counter:\n   after 2 failed deploy attempts of the SAME `origin/main` tip, auto-deploy DISABLES itself\n   (stop-file) + pages — it does NOT re-attempt the bad SHA every 2 min. An operator clears the\n   stop-file after fixing forward. (Because the gate is fail-closed, thrashing restarts would be worse\n   than pausing on a known-good image.)\n6. **Config validated BEFORE it touches the running Gerrit.** replication.config / g2p config are\n   parse-checked (`git config -f … --list`; g2p ini schema) BEFORE apply; a malformed config is\n   SKIPPED (prior config retained) + alarmed — a bad config never breaks live replication/CI dispatch.\n7. **Post-deploy pipeline-health gate.** deployed-sha advances only after a post-deploy check confirms\n   the end-to-end gate still works (bot health OK; a canary confirms review + CI dispatch paths).\n\n### Observability + back-out\nStructured deploy log (from→to SHA + components) + `rebar/host:deploy_errors` (host-probe grep of an\n`AUTODEPLOY_ERROR` marker, mirroring voter_errors) + a CloudWatch alarm w/ SNS action; the\ncircuit-breaker stop-file is itself alarmed. Back-out: `systemctl disable --now rebar-autodeploy.timer`;\nthe manual path (compose-up.sh / setup-*.sh) is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\nThe deploy orchestrator + systemd timer/service + stability guards + observability/back-out on the\nexisting compose stack. Reuses the idempotent setup/materialise appliers. refs/meta/config auto-apply\ndeferred (detect + signal). No change to gate semantics (S1/S2) or the feature-branch flow (88ab).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A change landing on `main` (post-gate + replicated) makes the running env reflect it with NO\n      manual action, ≤ 5 min; live-measured latency recorded\n- [ ] Idempotent + change-detected: a no-change run is a no-op; a relevant change re-applies ONLY the\n      changed component(s) — verified for review-bot code, replication.config, and g2p separately\n- [ ] review-bot rebuilt/restarted ONLY when its source-set changed (a docs-only `main` change does\n      NOT rebuild it); after a code change the running bot reflects it end-to-end (a merge change gets\n      the S2 merge-change tag from the auto-deployed bot)\n- [ ] STABILITY — blast radius: the `gerrit` container is provably untouched across a deploy;\n      `refs/meta/config` is never auto-modified; no Gerrit restart occurs (verified)\n- [ ] STABILITY — self-heal: a deliberately-broken review-bot image triggers the health check to FAIL\n      and rolls back to `:prev` (gate restored); deployed-sha not advanced (proven live)\n- [ ] STABILITY — circuit-breaker: 2 consecutive failed deploys of a SHA DISABLE auto-deploy + alarm\n      (no thrash); malformed replication/g2p config is rejected pre-apply (prior config retained)\n- [ ] STABILITY — in-flight: a review dropped by the restart window is recovered by the reconciler\n      backfill (delayed, not lost) — demonstrated\n- [ ] Concurrency: overlapping fires serialized by flock; deployed-sha written atomically only on success\n- [ ] project.config changes DETECTED + signalled (metric + log), not attempted (documented boundary)\n- [ ] Deploy log + `deploy_errors` metric + alarm applied; back-out (disable the timer) tested; manual\n      path still works\n- [ ] Live-verified end-to-end on the running box (a real `main` change auto-deploys within the window)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783076167767277001,"uuid":"2c2280e7-0094-496e-9530-815b8156f2d1"}